salim hoss and a social worker who cared for lebanons orphans and 
elderly died at american university hospital on saturday at age 61 
sources close to family who spoke on condition of anonymity 
said she suffered from lung cancer and diabetes 
mrs hoss supervised an orphanage and a home for the aged in 
moslem west beirut she also served on the boards of several 
schools that cared for needy children 
while many other politicians wives fled lebanons vicious 
15yearold civil war mrs hoss never left the country even 
though her husband narrowly escaped death in three bombings between 
1984 and 1989 
